sentences: On November 8, 1992, MTV began listing directors with the artist, song, and record company credits, because music videos had increasingly become an auteur's medium.
The most expensive video of all time was directed by Mark Romanek: Michael and Janet Jackson's "Scream" (1995), which cost $7 million to produce.
In 2003, Spike Jonze, Chris Cunningham, and Michel Gondry founded the Directors Label.
